If an insurer chooses to collect an overpayment made to a provider through a recoupment against future provider payments, the insurer shall, within twenty-four (24) months from the date that the insurer paid the claim, and at the actual time of recoupment give the provider written or electronic documentation that specifies:
The amount of the recoupment;
The covered person's name to whom the recoupment applies;
Patient identification number; and
Date of service.
